   <text>
      <body>
         <opener><address><addrLine>56 Fitzroy Av.,Dublin
            </addrLine></address>
            <dateline>15th October,1916</dateline>
            <salute>Dear Mrs <persName><persName ref="#p.1"> <idno type="URI" subtype="Wikidata"> https://www.rte.ie/archives/exhibitions/1993-easter-1916/portraits-1916/765442-portraits-1916-geraldine-dillon/></idno>Geraldine Plunkett Dillon</persName></persName></salute></opener>
         <p>I am sorry to be adding to your work and worry at such a time as this. Your preface I liked very much; what struck me most about it was its homeliness, sincerity, and its sense of the difficulty of reaching to the mastery of his instrument your brother showed. On the
            whole I agree with your criticism of his work, too. The whole book is very fine and will live.</p>
         <closer><salute>I am, dear Mrs. Dillon,
            Very gratefully yours, Peter McBrien</salute></closer>
         <postscript>
            <p>P.S. : I shall be at Larkfield about 8.15, p.m., next Tuesday, 17 th. : your sister
               must be blessing me. PMcB.</p>
         </postscript>
      </body>     
